cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks for image classification of time-series data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as deep learning and classification algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of feature representation and learning, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of Recurrence Plots, which is a technique used in information retrieval, suggesting that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the use of joint learning, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
